{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611763","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611763"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:15:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:15:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16240"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16240"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.26,0.04,0.39,0.17]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8931"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73397"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8931"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16240"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58863"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"377"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7662"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8133"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21253"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21255"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73397","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73397"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBreast cancer prognosis and treatment decisions are guided by various molecular markers that indicate tumour characteristics.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a common marker of tumour progression in breast cancer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alpha-fetoprotein level","Carbohydrate antigen 19-9","Prostate specific antigen","Ki-67 protein expression","Beta-human chorionic gonadotropin"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKi-67 protein expression\u003C/strong\u003E is an important proliferation marker in breast cancer. It is present during all active phases of the cell cycle (G1, S, G2, and M) but absent in resting cells (G0). Higher Ki-67 levels indicate more aggressive tumour growth and correlate with poorer prognosis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are tumour markers for other cancers:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha-fetoprotein\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily used as a marker for hepatocellular carcinoma and germ cell tumours\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECarbohydrate antigen 19-9\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with pancreatic cancer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBeta-human chorionic gonadotropin\u003C/strong\u003E is a marker for gestational trophoblastic disease and testicular cancer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProstate specific antigen\u003C/strong\u003E is specific to prostate cancer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EKi-67 scoring is particularly useful in breast cancer management as it helps determine the proliferative activity of tumour cells, which influences treatment decisions, especially regarding chemotherapy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ki-67 is a nuclear protein present during all active phases of cell division and serves as a marker of cellular proliferation in breast cancer.","Higher Ki-67 levels correlate with more aggressive breast cancer behaviour and poorer prognosis.","Ki-67 scoring helps guide treatment decisions in breast cancer management."],"references":["Inwald EC, Klinkhammer-Schalke M, Hofst\u00e4dter F, Zeman F, Koller M, Gerstenhauer M, Ortmann O. Ki-67 is a prognostic parameter in breast cancer patients: results of a large population-based cohort of a cancer registry. Breast Cancer Res Treat. 2013 Jun;139(2):539-52. doi: 10.1007/s10549-013-2560-8. Epub 2013 May 16. PMID: 23674192; PMCID: PMC3669503.","Soliman NA, Yussif SM. Ki-67 as a prognostic marker according to breast cancer molecular subtype. Cancer Biol Med. 2016 Dec;13(4):496-504. doi: 10.20892/j.issn.2095-3941.2016.0066. PMID: 28154782; PMCID: PMC5250608.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58863"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16240"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58863","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58863"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T15:18:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T08:03:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8931"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73397"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"po